column1: If you're voting in person VOTING CENTERS ARE OPEN! Because of Covid your polling place has probably changed this year - find one near you: https://t.co/OzN1ZKVGLj https://t.co/2CnnbmrbPD

We had an INCREDIBLE turnout at our (covid safe) volunteer events all across the Valley today! Team Harder is fired up! Don't miss out join us tomorrow to finish our FINAL weekend of action strong: https://t.co/0uhFv8Rtga https://t.co/7saQLEnPf4

I’m voting for Josh because he did a great job in his first two years. He works hard to actually help people and fights for important issues like health care immigration and recently the Covid-19 relief bill.  https://t.co/O2J3NM8quR
222239 Americans have died from the Coronavirus - and millions have lost their jobs. I've privately and publicly called on leadership from both parties to step up and get this deal DONE.

Today's #TeamHarder Spotlight: Ann Marie from Modesto!  "I'm voting for Josh because his town hall phone meetings during Covid 19 mean so much to me. Hearing his reassuring and encouraging voice and listening to the experts gives us the information to get through this pandemic." https://t.co/y6IRo8KcvW
Where is this sense of urgency when it comes to a COVID relief bill?? https://t.co/RZV7kyrtJa

TONIGHT: Join me for a virtual COVID roundtable to discuss how we can stay healthy and rebuild our economy. Join the conversation: https://t.co/wxLsT5FIbg
Once a Covid vaccine is ready - it needs to be FREE for everyone.

Yesterday we dropped off 10000 masks and checked in with our emergency services workers about our fire and Coronavirus response. These workers are literally lifesavers and we owe them big time. Helping out with masks is the least we can do! https://t.co/xqmhnNAtey
The best COVID treatment we have is more than $3000 WITH insurance. Especially during a global pandemic - no one should have to empty their wallet to get medicine.
Once a Coronavirus vaccine is ready - it needs to be FREE.
No more political games - we need to pass a clean COVID bill and get stimulus checks in people's hands now. https://t.co/BAFPCppvic
THIS is why I established my Latino COVID Task Force - so we can address these issues head on. https://t.co/zAEVsZYFa0

Our doctors and nurses are on the frontlines of the COVID fight. And we all owe them a debt of gratitude for putting their own health on the line to keep us safe. Share this post to show them some love!
The best treatment we have for Covid is more than $3000 WITH insurance. https://t.co/TPLAbJsC4b
Insurance companies shouldn't decide who lives and dies in a pandemic. Coronavirus tests treatments and eventually the vaccine MUST be free.
Social distance. Be safe. https://t.co/zYHCKnJK0L
Cases of Covid are SKYROCKETING in Stanislaus and San Joaquin Counties - and our hospitals are filling up fast. We NEED to take this seriously. Social distance.

As of today more than 130000 Americans have died from Coronavirus. We all have a part to play to stop this.

Coronavirus is changing every aspect of our lives including how we'll celebrate this Fourth of July weekend. How are you and your family spending the holiday?

Nursing homes are at the center of this pandemic - and we now know that the Coronavirus can spread through folks who don't show symptoms. Read more about my bill to guarantee EVERYONE at nursing homes is tested: https://t.co/W2PMUbFUWG
Would you believe that this week the Senate has taken six votes and not a single one has been on Coronavirus relief? Folks in the Valley need relief now!
Ag is an essential industry. Glad to see the White House took my advice and is finally giving our farmers a voice on the Coronavirus Task Force!  https://t.co/4oh3VtBfms

May is Mental Health Awareness Month - and we all know that the Coronavirus pandemic and the isolation that it's required is taking its toll on people. Know that you are not alone. If you or a loved one are in crisis please call 1-800-273-8255.
Betsy DeVos is at it again. We passed a bill to stop student loan payments during the Coronavirus but she's still snatching money from people. Unbelievable.  https://t.co/ndB7QAHD59

And he's not only helping folks sick with Coronavirus he's living separately from his family during this crisis to keep them safe.
